## ğŸš€ Development Guidelines

### Core Principles
1. **Static First**: No server-side rendering or dynamic functionality
2. **Performance**: Aim for Lighthouse score 95+ in all categories
3. **Accessibility**: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance
4. **Progressive Enhancement**: Works without JavaScript, enhanced with it
5. **Mobile First**: Responsive design starting from mobile viewport

### Content Management
- Use **Markdown** for all text content where possible
- Store content in separate `.md` files in `src/content/` or `docs/`
- Use Astro's content collections for structured content
- Keep copy focused on Portuguese non-profit mission and app benefits

### Component Development
```typescript
// Prefer React components for interactive elements
import { useState } from 'react';

export default function InteractiveButton() {
  const [clicked, setClicked] = useState(false);
  
  return (
    <button 
      className="gradient-button"
      onClick={() => setClicked(!clicked)}
    >
      Download Comfy
    </button>
  );
}
```

```astro
---
// Use Astro components for static content
interface Props {
  title: string;
  description: string;
}

const { title, description } = Astro.props;
---

<section class="feature-card">
  <h3>{title}</h3>
  <p>{description}</p>
</section>

<style>
.feature-card {
  background: linear-gradient(83.21deg, #3245ff 0%, #bc52ee 100%);
  /* Use design system colors */
}
</style>
```

### Styling Guidelines
- Use CSS custom properties for consistent theming
- Implement gradients as defined in design system
- Ensure proper contrast ratios for accessibility
- Use modern CSS features (Grid, Flexbox, backdrop-filter)
- Mobile-first responsive breakpoints

### File Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `HeroSection.astro`)
- Pages: lowercase with hyphens (e.g., `about-us.astro`)
- Assets: descriptive names (e.g., `comfy-app-preview.png`)
- Markdown files: UPPERCASE for docs (e.g., `DESIGN.md`)

